definitions.definition: A small French coin , originally of silver , afterwards of copper , worth 5 deniers ; also a silver coin of Henry V current in the parts of France then held by the English, worth about 8 pence [15th–17th century] .
The white spot in the centre of a target ; hence ( figuratively ) the object to which anything is directed or aimed , the range of such aim [since the 16th century] .
A lot by which nothing is gained ; a ticket in a lottery on which no prize is indicated [since the 16th century] .
An empty space ; a void , for example on a paper [since the 16th century] .

subdefinitions.definition: A space to be filled in on a form or template .
examples: Write your answers in the blanks .

subdefinitions.definition: Provisional words printed in italics (instead of blank spaces) in a bill before Parliament , being matters of practical detail , of which the final form is to be settled in committee [since the 19th century] .

definitions.definition: A document, paper, or form with spaces left blank to be filled in at the pleasure of the person to whom it is given (e.g. a blank charter , ballot , form , contract , etc.), or as the event may determine; a blank form [since the 16th century] .

subdefinitions.definition: An empty form without substance; anything insignificant; nothing at all [since the 17th century] .
An unprinted leaf of a book [20th century] .

definitions.definition: A piece of material roughly cut, forged, cast, etc. to the size and shape of the thing to be made, and ready for the finishing operations; ( coining ) the disc of metal before stamping [since the 16th century] .

subdefinitions.definition: Any article of glass on which subsequent processing is required [since the 19th century] .
The shaved wax ready for placing on a recording machine for making wax records with a stylus [20th century] .

definitions.definition: A vacant space, place , or period ; a void [since the 17th century] .
An empty space in one's memory ; a forgotten item or memory [since the 18th century] .
A dash written in place of an omitted letter or word
The space character; the character resulting from pressing the space bar on a keyboard .
A domino without points on one or both of its divisions .
Ellipsis of blank cartridge [since the 19th century] .
examples: It was an unloaded gun that fired only blanks.

definitions.definition: An ineffective effort which achieves nothing [since the 20th century] .

subdefinitions.definition: A sample for a control experiment that does not contain any of the analyte of interest, in order to deliberately produce a non-detection to verify that a detection is distinguishable from it.
